<paragraph id="2E57369EBC677057D0C6FC17FDC0DE13" blockId="5.[151,1437,903,2038]" pageId="5" pageNumber="6">
<emphasis id="1C9CEA8CBC677057D0C6FC17FEE0D8EB" bold="true" box="[201,354,973,997]" inLineHeading="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="6" reason="1">Morphology.</emphasis>
Male — Idiosoma L/W 2260/2060; integument papillose; postocularia particularly distant from preocularia, together with the lateral eyes forming the edges of a longitudinally rectangular field (
<figureCitation id="B6D32A1BBC677057D4E0FC35FACBDF09" box="[1263,1353,1007,1031]" captionStart="FIGURE 2" captionStartId="6.[151,249,993,1016]" captionTargetBox="[161,1430,200,966]" captionTargetId="figure-396@6.[151,1436,195,972]" captionTargetPageId="6" captionText="FIGURE 2A–B. Hydrachna cf. vaillanti K. Viets 1951, male, IR5-2011: A = genital field, with posterior coxae; B = frontal area. Scale bar = 100 µm." pageId="5" pageNumber="6">Fig. 2B</figureCitation>
); coxal field: L 866, W 1700, medial margin of Cx-III+IV concave, Cx-IV bearing one seta, posteromedial corner of Cx- IV extended with cleaver-shaped posterolaterally directed secondary sclerotization; genital field L/W 441/413, posteriorly extending beyond posterior margin of Cx-IV, deeply indented anteriorly, extending over the anterior third of the plate, gonopore long, extending over the posterior third of the plate (
<figureCitation id="B6D32A1BBC677057D413FBA0FBF4DF9C" box="[1052,1142,1146,1170]" captionStart="FIGURE 2" captionStartId="6.[151,249,993,1016]" captionTargetBox="[161,1430,200,966]" captionTargetId="figure-396@6.[151,1436,195,972]" captionTargetPageId="6" captionText="FIGURE 2A–B. Hydrachna cf. vaillanti K. Viets 1951, male, IR5-2011: A = genital field, with posterior coxae; B = frontal area. Scale bar = 100 µm." pageId="5" pageNumber="6">Fig. 2A</figureCitation>
); Ac small and numerous; ejaculatory complex L 375. Gnathosoma L 881, rostrum L 500, relatively long and curved (
<figureCitation id="B6D32A1BBC677057D4A2FB47FA85DFBB" box="[1197,1287,1181,1205]" captionStart="FIGURE 3" captionStartId="7.[151,249,1979,2002]" captionTargetBox="[163,1401,187,1944]" captionTargetId="figure-65@7.[151,1436,171,1963]" captionTargetPageId="7" captionText="FIGURE 3A–E. Hydrachna cf. vaillanti K. Viets 1951 (B, C, D — male, A, F, E — female), IR5-2011: A = genital and coxal field; B = I-L-5 and-6; C, F = gnathosoma and chelicera, lateral view; D–E = palp. Scale bars = 100 µm." pageId="5" pageNumber="6">Fig. 3C</figureCitation>
); chelicera L 1100; palp (
<figureCitation id="B6D32A1BBC677057D110FB65FEF9DFD9" box="[287,379,1215,1239]" captionStart="FIGURE 3" captionStartId="7.[151,249,1979,2002]" captionTargetBox="[163,1401,187,1944]" captionTargetId="figure-65@7.[151,1436,171,1963]" captionTargetPageId="7" captionText="FIGURE 3A–E. Hydrachna cf. vaillanti K. Viets 1951 (B, C, D — male, A, F, E — female), IR5-2011: A = genital and coxal field; B = I-L-5 and-6; C, F = gnathosoma and chelicera, lateral view; D–E = palp. Scale bars = 100 µm." pageId="5" pageNumber="6">Fig. 3D</figureCitation>
): total L 773; dL: P-1, 206; P-2, 181; P-3, 238; P-4, 93; P-5, 55; palp stout, P-1 bearing one dorsodistal seta, P-2 ventral margin slightly concave or straight. Legs: dL of I-L-2-6: 194, 138, 178, 194, 222; dL of IV-L: 246, 281, 222, 503, 441, 231.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="2E57369EBC677057D0C6FAFDFCB2DEE3" blockId="5.[151,1437,903,2038]" pageId="5" pageNumber="6">
Female (n = 2) — Idiosoma L/W 1810/1625; coxal field: L 770 
<emphasis id="1C9CEA8CBC677057D39EFAF2FC1DDE4E" bold="true" box="[913,927,1320,1344]" pageId="5" pageNumber="6">–</emphasis>
825, W 1590 
<emphasis id="1C9CEA8CBC677057D43EFAF2FBBDDE4E" bold="true" box="[1073,1087,1320,1344]" pageId="5" pageNumber="6">–</emphasis>
1720; genital field (
<figureCitation id="B6D32A1BBC677057D513FAFDFAF1DE31" box="[1308,1395,1319,1343]" captionStart="FIGURE 3" captionStartId="7.[151,249,1979,2002]" captionTargetBox="[163,1401,187,1944]" captionTargetId="figure-65@7.[151,1436,171,1963]" captionTargetPageId="7" captionText="FIGURE 3A–E. Hydrachna cf. vaillanti K. Viets 1951 (B, C, D — male, A, F, E — female), IR5-2011: A = genital and coxal field; B = I-L-5 and-6; C, F = gnathosoma and chelicera, lateral view; D–E = palp. Scale bars = 100 µm." pageId="5" pageNumber="6">Fig. 3A</figureCitation>
) L/ W 256 
<emphasis id="1C9CEA8CBC677057D0EBFA91FF70DE6D" bold="true" box="[228,242,1355,1379]" pageId="5" pageNumber="6">–</emphasis>
269/334 
<emphasis id="1C9CEA8CBC677057D141FA91FEDEDE6D" bold="true" box="[334,348,1355,1379]" pageId="5" pageNumber="6">–</emphasis>
373, deeply indented anteriorly extending anterior half of the plate, the “modified acetabulum” not anterior to but between posterior setal fields; gnathosoma (
<figureCitation id="B6D32A1BBC677057D35EFAB7FC20DE8B" box="[849,930,1389,1413]" captionStart="FIGURE 3" captionStartId="7.[151,249,1979,2002]" captionTargetBox="[163,1401,187,1944]" captionTargetId="figure-65@7.[151,1436,171,1963]" captionTargetPageId="7" captionText="FIGURE 3A–E. Hydrachna cf. vaillanti K. Viets 1951 (B, C, D — male, A, F, E — female), IR5-2011: A = genital and coxal field; B = I-L-5 and-6; C, F = gnathosoma and chelicera, lateral view; D–E = palp. Scale bars = 100 µm." pageId="5" pageNumber="6">Fig. 3F</figureCitation>
) L 640 
<emphasis id="1C9CEA8CBC677057D3FBFAB7FB80DE8B" bold="true" box="[1012,1026,1389,1413]" pageId="5" pageNumber="6">–</emphasis>
680, rostrum L 330 
<emphasis id="1C9CEA8CBC677057D4D6FAB7FB65DE8B" bold="true" box="[1241,1255,1389,1413]" pageId="5" pageNumber="6">–</emphasis>
370; chelicera L 1000; palp (
<figureCitation id="B6D32A1BBC677057D12DFA55FEF9DEA9" box="[290,379,1423,1447]" captionStart="FIGURE 3" captionStartId="7.[151,249,1979,2002]" captionTargetBox="[163,1401,187,1944]" captionTargetId="figure-65@7.[151,1436,171,1963]" captionTargetPageId="7" captionText="FIGURE 3A–E. Hydrachna cf. vaillanti K. Viets 1951 (B, C, D — male, A, F, E — female), IR5-2011: A = genital and coxal field; B = I-L-5 and-6; C, F = gnathosoma and chelicera, lateral view; D–E = palp. Scale bars = 100 µm." pageId="5" pageNumber="6">Fig. 3E</figureCitation>
): total L 704 
<emphasis id="1C9CEA8CBC677057D21EFA4AFD9DDEA6" bold="true" box="[529,543,1424,1448]" pageId="5" pageNumber="6">–</emphasis>
707; dL: P-1, 184 
<emphasis id="1C9CEA8CBC677057D2E4FA4AFD7BDEA6" bold="true" box="[747,761,1424,1448]" pageId="5" pageNumber="6">–</emphasis>
194; P-2, 150; P-3, 219 
<emphasis id="1C9CEA8CBC677057D408FA4AFB97DEA6" bold="true" box="[1031,1045,1424,1448]" pageId="5" pageNumber="6">–</emphasis>
225; P-4, 91 
<emphasis id="1C9CEA8CBC677057D4ACFA4AFB33DEA6" bold="true" box="[1187,1201,1424,1448]" pageId="5" pageNumber="6">–</emphasis>
95; P-5, 47 
<emphasis id="1C9CEA8CBC677057D53EFA4AFABDDEA6" bold="true" box="[1329,1343,1424,1448]" pageId="5" pageNumber="6">–</emphasis>
56; palp stout, P-4 more slender than in male (age dependant?). Legs: dL of I-L-2-6: 181, 113, 141, 156, 185; dL of IV-L: 231 
<emphasis id="1C9CEA8CBC677057D0CEFA0FFF4DDEE3" bold="true" box="[193,207,1493,1517]" pageId="5" pageNumber="6">–</emphasis>
234, 256 
<emphasis id="1C9CEA8CBC677057D13EFA0FFEBDDEE3" bold="true" box="[305,319,1493,1517]" pageId="5" pageNumber="6">–</emphasis>
281, 200 
<emphasis id="1C9CEA8CBC677057D1AEFA0FFE2DDEE3" bold="true" box="[417,431,1493,1517]" pageId="5" pageNumber="6">–</emphasis>
223, 419 
<emphasis id="1C9CEA8CBC677057D21EFA0FFD9DDEE3" bold="true" box="[529,543,1493,1517]" pageId="5" pageNumber="6">–</emphasis>
422, 350 
<emphasis id="1C9CEA8CBC677057D28EFA0FFD0DDEE3" bold="true" box="[641,655,1493,1517]" pageId="5" pageNumber="6">–</emphasis>
363, 209 
<emphasis id="1C9CEA8CBC677057D2FEFA0FFD7DDEE3" bold="true" box="[753,767,1493,1517]" pageId="5" pageNumber="6">–</emphasis>
225.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="2E57369EBC677057D0C6FA2DFAF3DD76" blockId="5.[151,1437,903,2038]" pageId="5" pageNumber="6">
Deutonymph (collected together with adults of 
<taxonomicName id="E9E84D1DBC677057D2D4FA22FC63DD1E" authorityName="K. Viets" authorityYear="1951" box="[731,993,1527,1552]" class="Arachnida" family="Hydrachnidae" genus="Hydrachna" kingdom="Animalia" order="Trombidiformes" pageId="5" pageNumber="6" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="vaillanti">
