<subSubSection id="66F26515BC677057D0C6F959FDD3DCFB" pageId="5" pageNumber="6" type="discussion">
<paragraph id="2E57369EBC677057D0C6F959FEB9DCDC" blockId="5.[151,1437,903,2038]" pageId="5" pageNumber="6">
<emphasis id="1C9CEA8CBC677057D0C6F959FEBEDD95" bold="true" box="[201,316,1667,1691]" inLineHeading="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="6" reason="1">Remarks.</emphasis>
The population from Sistan va Baluchestan belongs to the 
<taxonomicName id="E9E84D1DBC677057D3DFF959FB5CDD95" authorityName="Koenike" authorityYear="1903" box="[976,1246,1667,1691]" class="Arachnida" family="Hydrachnidae" genus="Hydrachna" kingdom="Animalia" order="Trombidiformes" pageId="5" pageNumber="6" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="processifera">
<emphasis id="1C9CEA8CBC677057D3DFF959FB5CDD95" box="[976,1246,1667,1691]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="6">Hydrachna processifera</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
group of species which includes 
<taxonomicName id="E9E84D1DBC677057D142F97CFD2CDDB3" authority="Koenike, 1903" authorityName="Koenike" authorityYear="1903" box="[333,686,1701,1725]" class="Arachnida" family="Hydrachnidae" genus="Hydrachna" kingdom="Animalia" order="Trombidiformes" pageId="5" pageNumber="6" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="processifera">
<emphasis id="1C9CEA8CBC677057D142F97CFE79DDB3" box="[333,507,1701,1725]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="6">H. processifera</emphasis>
Koenike, 1903
</taxonomicName>
and several little documented species (e.g. 
<taxonomicName id="E9E84D1DBC677057D4A3F97CFF50DDEE" authority="Laska, 1964" authorityName="Laska" authorityYear="1964" class="Arachnida" family="Hydrachnidae" genus="Hydrachna" kingdom="Animalia" order="Trombidiformes" pageId="5" pageNumber="6" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="danubialis">
<emphasis id="1C9CEA8CBC677057D4A3F97CFACADDB3" box="[1196,1352,1701,1725]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="6">H. danubialis</emphasis>
Láska, 1964
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName id="E9E84D1DBC677057D0D2F913FEDFDDEE" authorityName="K. Viets" authorityYear="1951" box="[221,349,1736,1760]" class="Arachnida" family="Hydrachnidae" genus="Hydrachna" kingdom="Animalia" order="Trombidiformes" pageId="5" pageNumber="6" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="vaillanti">
<emphasis id="1C9CEA8CBC677057D0D2F913FEDFDDEE" box="[221,349,1736,1760]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="6">H. vaillanti</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName id="E9E84D1DBC677057D19BF913FD71DDEE" authority="Bader, 1981" authorityName="Bader" authorityYear="1981" box="[404,755,1736,1760]" class="Arachnida" family="Hydrachnidae" genus="Hydrachna" kingdom="Animalia" order="Trombidiformes" pageId="5" pageNumber="6" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="sepasgozariani">
<emphasis id="1C9CEA8CBC677057D19BF913FDE2DDD1" box="[404,608,1736,1760]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="6">H. sepasgozariani</emphasis>
Bader, 1981
</taxonomicName>
). Due to the similar shape of the male genital field (minor in dimensions, anterior margin more elongated, extending over 1/3 of the genital field) the specimens from Sistan va Baluchestan most resemble 
<taxonomicName id="E9E84D1DBC677057D1C0F8D7FD33DC2B" authorityName="K. Viets" authorityYear="1951" box="[463,689,1805,1829]" class="Arachnida" family="Hydrachnidae" genus="Hydrachna" kingdom="Animalia" order="Trombidiformes" pageId="5" pageNumber="6" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="vaillanti">
<emphasis id="1C9CEA8CBC677057D1C0F8D7FD33DC2B" box="[463,689,1805,1829]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="6">Hydrachna vaillanti</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, a species known from a single male from 
<collectingCountry id="56FF760EBC677057D49DF8D7FB64DC2B" box="[1170,1254,1805,1829]" name="Algeria" pageId="5" pageNumber="6">Algeria</collectingCountry>
(central Sahara, K. 
<bibRefCitation id="4A794B6FBC677057D0B6F8EAFEB4DC46" author="Viets, K." box="[185,310,1840,1864]" pageId="5" pageNumber="6" pagination="285 - 303" refId="ref34372" refString="Viets, K. (1951) Hydrachnellae (Acari) aus den franzosischen Alpen und aus Afrika. Zoologischer Anzeiger, 147 (11 / 12), 285 - 303." type="journal article" year="1951">Viets 1951</bibRefCitation>
). However, as mentioned by 
<bibRefCitation id="4A794B6FBC677057D272F8EAFCE3DC46" author="Davids, K. &amp; Di Sabatino, A. &amp; Gerecke, R. &amp; Gledhill, T. &amp; Smit, H." box="[637,865,1840,1864]" pageId="5" pageNumber="6" pagination="36 - 64" refId="ref33011" refString="Davids, K., Di Sabatino, A., Gerecke, R., Gledhill, T. &amp; Smit, H. (2005) On the taxonomy of water mites (Acari: Hydrachnidia) described from the Palaearctic, part 1: Hydrachnidae, Limnocharidae and Eylaidae. Zootaxa, 1061, 36 - 64." type="journal article" year="2005">
Davids 
<emphasis id="1C9CEA8CBC677057D2DBF8EBFC84DC46" box="[724,774,1840,1864]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="6">et al</emphasis>
. (2005)
</bibRefCitation>
, these features in the 
<typeStatus id="F153883CBC677057D45BF8EAFB06DC46" box="[1108,1156,1840,1864]" pageId="5" pageNumber="6">type</typeStatus>
specimen of 
<taxonomicName id="E9E84D1DBC677057D513F8EBFA1EDC46" authorityName="K. Viets" authorityYear="1951" box="[1308,1436,1840,1864]" class="Arachnida" family="Hydrachnidae" genus="Hydrachna" kingdom="Animalia" order="Trombidiformes" pageId="5" pageNumber="6" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="vaillanti">
<emphasis id="1C9CEA8CBC677057D513F8EBFA1EDC46" box="[1308,1436,1840,1864]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="6">H. vaillanti</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
might be an individual aberration. The morphological homogenity of specimens from Sistan va Baluchestan suggests that they represent a distinct taxon. Without information on the population variability of 
<taxonomicName id="E9E84D1DBC677057D4C8F8ACFAC4DC83" authorityName="K. Viets" authorityYear="1951" box="[1223,1350,1909,1933]" class="Arachnida" family="Hydrachnidae" genus="Hydrachna" kingdom="Animalia" order="Trombidiformes" pageId="5" pageNumber="6" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="vaillanti">
<emphasis id="1C9CEA8CBC677057D4C8F8ACFAC4DC83" box="[1223,1350,1909,1933]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="6">H. vaillanti</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, and in view of the large geographical distance of our records, this assignment is based mainly on non-identity with alternative species.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="2E57369EBC677057D0C6F807FDD3DCFB" blockId="5.[151,1437,903,2038]" box="[201,593,2013,2038]" pageId="5" pageNumber="6">
<emphasis id="1C9CEA8CBC677057D0C6F807FEAEDCF8" bold="true" box="[201,300,2013,2038]" inLineHeading="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="6" reason="1">Habitat.</emphasis>
Standing water (
<figureCitation id="B6D32A1BBC677057D1E5F807FDC6DCFB" box="[490,580,2013,2037]" captionStart="FIGURE 8" captionStartId="13.[151,249,1919,1942]" captionTargetBox="[190,1398,193,1904]" captionTargetId="figure-79@13.[188,1398,193,1904]" captionTargetPageId="13" captionText="FIGURE 8A–B. Standing water habitats: A — pool in Gerdoig village (collecting site of Hydrachna cf. vaillanti, H. globosa lacerata, Diplodontus silvestrii and Limnesia pinguipalpis, and locus typicus of Hydrachna sistanica); B — pool in saline stream near Khorgoo village (collecting site of Haloaxonopsis salina and locus typicus of Limnesia diversipes). Photos. V. Pešić." pageId="5" pageNumber="6">Fig. 8A</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
